</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-25_ pf-text-1">Research by the Natural Learning Initiative indicates that children who engage in regular outdoor play exhibit improved cognitive, social, and emotional development.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-27_ pf-text-1">A study by the University of Exeter found that children who spend time outdoors have better concentration and behaviour in the classroom.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-29_ pf-text-1">The Health and Safety Executive (HSE) emphasises the importance of managing risks in outdoor learning environments to ensure children's safety.
</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-jXbVAB kNtuek pf-31_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bDoQz cmNGeH pf-32_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-33_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key definitions
</h3><p class="sc-kAkozD iOjmJ pf-35_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><strong>Active outdoor learning</strong> - A pedagogical approach that involves engaging children in physical activities and play in natural or outdoor settings. It promotes physical health, social skills, and cognitive development.<br><br><strong>Early Years Foundation Stage (EYFS)</strong> - A statutory framework in the UK that sets standards for the learning, development, and care of children from birth to age five.<br>
<br><strong>Health and Safety Executive (HSE)</strong> - A UK government agency responsible for regulating and enforcing workplace health, safety, and welfare, including in early years settings.
<br>
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-jXbVAB kNtuek pf-37_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bDoQz cmNGeH pf-38_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-39_ pf-heading-1-h3">Recommended best practices for implementation
</h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-41_ pf-heading-1-h3">Understanding the legislation
</h3><p class="sc-kAkozD iOjmJ pf-43_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The EYFS framework mandates that early years providers must ensure children have daily access to outdoor play. This requirement is rooted in recognising that outdoor learning environments offer unique opportunities for children to explore, take risks, and develop crucial life skills.
</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-45_ pf-heading-1-h3">Key points from the EYFS framework
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dPZUdm cBqcmb pf-47_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-48_ pf-text-1">Providers must plan for and provide outdoor activities to promote physical development.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-50_ pf-text-1">Risk assessments must be conducted regularly to ensure the safety of outdoor spaces.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-52_ pf-text-1">Staff should be trained to handle potential emergencies effectively in first aid and risk management.
</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-54_ pf-heading-1-h3">Creating a safe and stimulating outdoor environment
</h3><p class="sc-kAkozD iOjmJ pf-56_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">To implement effective active outdoor learning, nurseries must create safe, stimulating environments that encourage exploration and play. This involves careful planning and adherence to health and safety guidelines.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-jXbVAB kNtuek pf-58_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bDoQz cmNGeH pf-59_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-60_ pf-heading-1-h3">Steps to create an effective outdoor learning environment
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dPZUdm cBqcmb pf-62_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-63_ pf-text-1"><strong>Conduct thorough risk assessments</strong> - Regularly assess outdoor areas to identify and mitigate potential hazards.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-65_ pf-text-1"><strong>Design engaging outdoor spaces </strong>- Incorporate natural elements such as plants, sand, and water to stimulate children's senses and curiosity.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-67_ pf-text-1"><strong>Provide appropriate equipment</strong> - Ensure outdoor play equipment is safe, age-appropriate, and well-maintained.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-69_ pf-text-1"><strong>Train staff</strong> - Equip staff with the necessary skills and knowledge to supervise outdoor activities and manage risks effectively.
</li></ul></div></div></div><div class="sc-jXbVAB kNtuek pf-71_ pf-r pf-c-lm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-bDoQz cmNGeH pf-72_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-73_ pf-heading-1-h3">Integrating outdoor learning into the curriculum
</h3><p class="sc-kAkozD iOjmJ pf-75_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Integrating outdoor learning into the early years curriculum enhances children's learning experiences and supports their overall development. This requires thoughtful planning and a commitment to making outdoor activities integral to daily routines.
</p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-cmaqZA fXrIOS pf-77_ pf-heading-1-h3">Strategies for curriculum integration
</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-dPZUdm cBqcmb pf-79_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-80_ pf-text-1"><strong>Thematic planning </strong>- Align outdoor activities with curriculum themes to reinforce learning objectives.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-82_ pf-text-1"><strong>Flexible timetables</strong> - Allocate specific times for outdoor play, allowing children to engage in unstructured and structured activities.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-eBHgEO eUYsjc pf-84_ pf-text-1"><strong>Observation and Assessment</strong> - Use outdoor learning opportunities to observe children's development and assess their progress in various areas.
